  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Take heed unto yourselves,.... Since he should not be long with them, to advise, instruct, and caution them: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "lest ye forget the covenant of the Lord your God, which he made with you; what that required of them, and what was promised unto them on the performance of it, and what they must expect should they break it, and particularly be so forgetful of it, and the first articles in it, as follows: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and make you a graven image, or the likeness of anything which the Lord thy God hath forbidden thee; a graven image in the likeness of men or women, of any beast on the earth, or fowl in heaven, or fish in the sea. ",
        "children": [
          {
