  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Keil and Delitzsch Biblical Commentary on the Old Testament",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The bringing of Israel out of Egypt reminds Moses of the end, viz., Canaan, and leads him to mention again how the Lord had refused him permission to enter into this good land; and to this he adds the renewed warning not to forget the covenant or make any image of God, since Jehovah, as a jealous God, would never tolerate this. The swearing attributed to God in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Deuteronomy 4:21",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " is neither mentioned in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Numbers 20",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " nor at the announcement of Moses' death in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Numbers 27:12",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".; but it is not to be called in question on that account, as Knobel supposes. It is perfectly obvious from ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Deuteronomy 3:23",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". that all the details are not given in the historical account of the event referred to. כּל תּמוּנת פּסל, \"image of a form of all that Jehovah has commanded,\" sc., not to be made (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Deuteronomy 4:16-18",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). \"A consuming fire\" (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Deuteronomy 4:24",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "): this epithet is applied to God with special reference to the manifestation of His glory in burning fire (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 24:17",
        "children": []
      },
